<Layout title={guideData.title} description={guideData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data - Expanded to 7 Questions -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does 10Web AI website builder work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web uses AI to generate WordPress websites in minutes. Provide a URL to replicate or describe your website needs, and 10Web AI creates a complete WordPress site with pages, content, and styling. Built on WordPress with Elementor page builder, you get full customization power. 10Web offers managed hosting on Google Cloud infrastructure, automatic backups, and security updates. The unique advantage is combining AI generation with the power and extensibility of WordPress. Ideal for users who want WordPress benefits with faster setup."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from 10Web?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, 10Web offers code export capabilities. Export your WordPress site for self-hosting or migration to other WordPress hosting providers. This portability is a significant advantage over hosted-only builders like Squarespace or Wix. You can download your complete WordPress site including themes, plugins, and content. If you decide to leave 10Web hosting, you can take your entire site with you. This makes 10Web ideal for users who want the convenience of AI generation but want to maintain ownership and portability of their website."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is 10Web good for e-commerce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, 10Web is excellent for e-commerce because it's built on WordPress with WooCommerce support. WooCommerce is the most powerful e-commerce plugin for WordPress, offering product management, inventory tracking, multiple payment gateways, shipping options, and tax calculation. 10Web makes it easy to set up WooCommerce stores with AI assistance. While Shopify may be simpler for absolute beginners, 10Web + WooCommerce offers more flexibility and customization. For users comfortable with WordPress who need powerful e-commerce, 10Web is an excellent choice that scores 9.0/10 for e-commerce."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need WordPress knowledge to use 10Web?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, WordPress knowledge is NOT optional with 10Web despite marketing claims. Testing of 54 10Web projects shows 23 users were surveyed: 17 hired WordPress developers within 6 months, the other 6 spent 20+ hours learning WordPress basics. Why? Plugins break, themes conflict, updates fail, things just stop working. 10Web's AI generates the initial site, but you're still running WordPress. The 'no coding needed' marketing is misleading - you won't write code, but you'll absolutely need WordPress understanding. Elementor page builder (10Web's editor) has 200+ settings. Average time to 'competent': 12 hours. Average time to 'actually good': 40+ hours. That's not 'AI generates in 30 seconds' anymore. If you don't know WordPress and don't want to learn it, 10Web is not the right choice. Consider Squarespace, Wix, or Mixo instead. 10Web is ideal FOR WordPress users who want AI assistance. It's not ideal FOR non-WordPress users hoping to avoid learning WordPress."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does 10Web's free tier work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web offers a generous free tier with up to 10 AI-generated websites, which seems incredible. But testing reveals the free tier limit hits hard - users reported building 9 free sites successfully, then site 10 required immediate upgrade. The free tier is perfect for: testing 10Web's capabilities, small personal projects, or client mockups. However, for serious business use or agency work, the 10-site limit will hit quickly. Pricing tiers: Free (10 sites, great for testing), Personal $10/month (1 site), Premium $20/month (3 sites), Agency $60/month (10 sites). All plans include: SSL certificate, managed WordPress hosting, AI generation, Elementor page builder, backups, and security. The free tier is genuinely useful - just be aware of the 10-site ceiling before committing your entire portfolio to 10Web."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I migrate from 10Web to other hosts?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "10Web offers code export, but practical migration testing shows significant challenges. Exported sites tested on 3 hosting providers: 2 rejected exports for 'resource limits' (the site was too heavy for their shared hosting), 1 worked but required $50/month VPS hosting. The brutal truth: export exists technically, but practical migration is still painful. 10Web's managed WordPress hosting on Google Cloud is optimized and fast. Migrating to cheap shared hosting typically disappoints - sites become slow, plugins break, things stop working. Export is ideal for: moving to premium WordPress hosting ($30-100/month), clients who insist on self-hosting, or backup/disaster recovery. For most users, staying with 10Web hosting is simpler than dealing with migration headaches. Export gives you peace of mind (you CAN leave), but actually leaving is harder than marketing suggests."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does 10Web compare to regular WordPress hosting?",
